All the old Airport films have vanished from the PirateBay! Even if they are old and camp and passÃƒÆ’Ã‚Â© compared to modern action films, they are still funny to watch -- especially for us who are interested in airplane history. I am old enough to remember seeing them all in the cinema theatres when they were new, and there was nothing camp about them then. But today, it feels kind of embarassing to have PAID to watch old stars like George Kennedy.

Alas, the production company has not bothered to transfer the cinema surround sound to all the DVDs, so several still have only Dolby Mono.

I found this torrent from Demonoid with all of the films, here is a survey:

Airport (1970)  &lt;a href=&quot;
